page_0: "This plan couldn't have worked better if I'd come up with it myself. Vivianne's idea to play on the feelings of that poor sap has paid off wonderfully. I thought a man of his skill wouldn't be that gullible, but darling Vivianne clearly knew him better than I! Not only did he locate the crystal sword where we could not, but he proved most easy to dispose of in the old sewage works beneath the mountain. After the plan's success, it was just a matter of ordering the men to retake the castle through the old sewer tunnels. Grent didn't know what had hit him. The treasure has all been brought aboard now, so we shall set off upon the morrow when the rest of the crew are back from shore leave."
